            "type": "image",
            "title": "Contractual Rights and Obligations in a Transaction",
            "metadata": "Contract law, buyer rights, seller obligations, option contract, financial instrument, legal framework",
            "data": "The image is a flowchart illustrating the contractual relationship between a buyer and a seller in a transaction involving an option or right. At the top, two main boxes represent the \"Buyer\" (买方) and the \"Seller\" (卖方). An arrow labeled \"Buyer pays seller a certain amount of rights fee\" (买方向卖方支付一定权利金) connects them bidirectionally, indicating a financial exchange. Below the buyer, text states \"Buyer's right can be abandoned\" (买方权利可以放弃), with a downward arrow leading to a purple box stating \"Buyer may abandon execution of contract content\" (买方可放弃执行合约内容). Below the seller, text states \"Seller's obligation cannot be abandoned\" (卖方义务无法放弃), with a downward arrow leading to a purple box stating \"Seller must execute contract content\" (卖方必须执行合约内容). A horizontal arrow between the two purple boxes is labeled \"If buyer abandons contract execution, buyer loses paid rights fee\" (买方放弃执行合同时损失其支付的权利金). The diagram visually emphasizes the asymmetry: the buyer holds a discretionary right to forgo the contract, while the seller is bound by a mandatory obligation, with the buyer's payment serving as the cost of this option.",
