            "data": "The table compares digital asset futures and traditional futures across four key attributes: 1) Market discovery value: Digital asset futures are limited to BTC only, while traditional futures have stronger market discovery value. 2) Risk hedging: Digital asset futures cannot hedge against market risks, whereas traditional futures can. 3) Market correlation: Digital asset futures have a weaker correlation with the spot market, while traditional futures have a stronger correlation. 4) Hedging capability: Digital asset futures do not support hedging, while traditional futures do. This comparison highlights the structural and functional differences between the two types of futures markets.",
