        {
            "type": "table",
            "title": "Comparison of BitMEX and OKEx Futures Platforms",
            "metadata": "BitMEX, OKEx, futures trading, contract types, leverage, margin requirements, perpetual contracts",
            "data": "The table provides a side-by-side comparison of the key features of BitMEX and OKEx futures trading platforms. In terms of contract types, BitMEX offers contracts for eight currencies and over ten types of products, while OKEx provides contracts for eight currencies and twenty-four types of products. Regarding leverage, BitMEX allows users to set their own leverage up to 100x, whereas OKEx only offers fixed leverage options of 10x and 20x. For margin requirements, BitMEX calculates it as the contract size divided by the estimated value of the underlying digital asset at the time of settlement, while OKEx calculates it as the value of the digital asset at the time of settlement divided by the leverage multiplier. Finally, regarding perpetual contracts, BitMEX supports them, but OKEx does not.",
